Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) is a managed Kubernetes platform used to deploy, manage, and scale containerized applications.

It automates container orchestration tasks such as scaling, load balancing, and self-healing.

For example, AKS can automatically restart failed containers and distribute traffic across multiple instances.

A real-life use case is large-scale applications like streaming platforms or e-commerce systems.

Another example is enterprise microservices architectures requiring high scalability and reliability.

AKS provides full control and flexibility for complex container workloads.
